<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-25 00:53 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Car plunges off oceanfront parking deck, killing 4 NYC women  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   VIRGINIA BEACH, Va. (AP) - A car plunged off the fifth-floor
parking deck of an oceanfront motel Sunday, killing four New York
women.
</P>
<P>
   The accident occurred during the resort city's busy Neptune
Festival weekend, a post-summer vacation celebration intended
mainly for local residents. The car landed on its roof just yards
from a carnival set up on the beach for the weekend.
</P>
<P>
   The victims were identified as driver Joan Ellen Walsh, 56, Mary
Ann Going, 60, Kathleen Mollick, 63, and Mary Ann Dono, 60. They
were from Brooklyn and Queens. No one on the ground was hurt.
</P>
<P>
   The car drove through a cinderblock retaining wall in the
parking deck, police said. Investigators were still trying to
determine the cause of the accident, which occurred shortly after
12:30 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   The parking deck at the Sandcastle Oceanfront Motel is at
Atlantic Avenue and 14th Street. Atlantic Avenue is the main
north-south road that runs parallel to the resort beach and
Boardwalk and is lined with hotels, restaurants and gift shops.
</P>
<P>
   Because of the extensive damage to the car, authorities did not
attempt to remove the bodies at the scene. Instead, the wreckage
was covered, and the car with the victims still inside was taken by
truck to a secure lot. The bodies will be taken to the medical
examiner's office in Norfolk.
</P>
<P>
   George Angelis, who was operating a Ferris wheel at the nearby
carnival, said he heard an engine revving and looked up to see the
car fall.
</P>
<P>
   ''It sounded like somebody might have tried to put the brakes
on, but their foot slipped off and hit the accelerator instead,''
Angelis said. ''I looked up and saw the blocks coming down. It was
kind of like slow motion as it flipped off of the ramp.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
