<HEADLINE> Four Dead After Car Plunges Off Deck  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   VIRGINIA BEACH, Va. (AP) -- A car plunged off the 5th-floor
parking deck of an oceanfront motel Sunday, killing four New York
women.
</P>
<P>
   The accident occurred during the resort city's busy Neptune
Festival weekend, a post-summer vacation celebration intended
mainly for local residents. The car landed on its roof just yards
from a carnival set up on the beach for the weekend.
</P>
<P>
   Don Rimer, a Virginia Beach police spokesman, identified the
victims as Joan Ellen Walsh, 56, the driver, of New York City; Mary
Ann Going, 60, of East Elmhurst, N.Y.; and Kathleen M. Mollick, 63,
and Mary Ann Dono, 60, both of New York City.
</P>
<P>
   All of the victims were riding in the car. No one on the ground
was hurt.
</P>
<P>
   Rimer said the car drove through a cinderblock retaining wall in
the parking deck. Investigators were still trying to determine the
cause of the accident, which occurred shortly about 12:30 p.m.
</P>
