<HEADLINE> Indiana Celebrates James Dean  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   FAIRMOUNT, Ind. (AP) -- Thousands of people flocked to this
east-central Indiana city to pay tribute to the late actor James
Dean -- including another hometown hero who spends a lot of time
front of the camera.
</P>
<P>
   ''CBS Evening News'' correspondent Phil Jones returned to his
native Fairmount to serve as parade grand marshal at the weekend's
''Jimmy Dean Days.''
</P>
<P>
   Before Saturday's parade began, Jones gave one of his seven Emmy
awards to the Fairmount Historical Museum.
</P>
