<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dow Gains 27; Nasdaq Climbs 53  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- The Dow Jones industrial average is up 27 points
in today's early going. Advancing issues on the New York Stock
Exchange hold a 9-7 lead over decliners.
</P>
<P>
   The Nasdaq Composite Index is ahead 53 points and the Standard &AMP;
Poor's 500 Stock Index is up six points.
</P>
<P>
   Wall Street is being greeted with a steady performance by the
euro today and a decline in crude oil prices.
</P>
<P>
   Central banks stepped in Friday to boost the troubled European
currency and President Clinton announced over the weekend that he
would release some of the country's strategic oil reserve.
</P>
<P>
   The weak euro and rising crude prices have been putting a damper
on the market's performance this month.
</P>
<P>
   So, a change in the recent trend is seen as welcome news on Wall
Street.
</P>
<P>
   The market gets some economic information this morning, when the
National Association of Realtors releases its August report on home
resales.
</P>
</TEXT>
