<HEADLINE> Nasdaq Drops 12; Dow Sheds 18  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks slipped Monday after faltering in a bid
to extend Friday's rebound from a market-jolting profit warning by
Intel.
</P>
<P>
   In afternoon trading on Wall Street, the technology-led Nasdaq
composite index fell 12.19 to 3,791.57 despite an early gain of
nearly 65 points.
</P>
<P>
   The Dow Jones industrial average was down 18.13 at 10,829.24
after giving back most of an early 50-point gain, while the
Standard &AMP; Poor's 500-stock index was off 3.27 at 1,445.45 and the
Russell 2000 index of smaller companies slipped 0.01 to 518.81.
</P>
<P>
   Sun Microsystems was up $2.69 a share at $120.69 on the Nasdaq
but its gain was offset by the poor performance of other tech
stocks. Cisco Systems was down $2.38 at $57.94, and Microsoft
slipped $2.19 at $61.06. Intel fell $1.88 to $46.06.
</P>
<P>
   Micron Technology was down $2.25 at $49.25. Lucent fell $1.19 to
$30.81.
</P>
<P>
   But financial shares moved higher, with J.P. Morgan up 94 cents
at $168.63, Citigroup up $1.63 to $54.38 and American Express up
$1.38 at $60.13.
</P>
<P>
   Among the day's big movers, Ciena rose $9.69 to $130.44 after
the maker of optical network equipment announced a major order from
Korea Telecom. Sprint PCS rose $3.75 to $31.75 after Lehman
Brothers upgraded its rating of the mobile phone company.
</P>
<P>
   The market's advance came as world finance officials, facing the
twin threats of soaring oil prices and a weak European currency,
gathered in Prague for the annual meetings of the International
Monetary Fund and the World Bank. The finance ministers spent the
weekend putting together joint statements intended to show their
resolve to deal with the two problems, which are threatening
current global prosperity.
</P>
<P>
   Declining issues outnumbered advancers by a narrow margin on the
Nasdaq Stock Market, while decliners took the lead on the New York
Stock Exchange.
</P>
<P>
   NYSE volume came to 782.73 million shares, down from 920.59
million at the same point on Friday.
</P>
