<HEADLINE> Business news in brief from around New Jersey  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   PARSIPANNY, N.J. (AP) - Novartis Pharmaceuticals has awarded
Integrated Communications Corp. the promotion responsibility for
the new epilepsy drug Trileptal, the advertising agency said
Monday.
</P>
<P>
   Integrated Communications also recently was awarded contracts by
Novartis to promote Lamisil tablets, an oral treatment for toenail
fungus; Exelon, a new product for the treatment of Alzheimer's
disease; and a new asthma drug awaiting FDA approval.
</P>
<P>
   Integrated Communications Corp. is part of the Lowe Healthcare
Worldwide network and the Interpublic Group of companies.
</P>
<P>
   MORRIS TOWNSHIP, N.J. (AP) - Honeywell has promoted James T.
Porter to the new position of senior vice president and chief
administrative officer, the company said Monday.
</P>
<P>
   Porter has been Honeywell's senior vice president of information
systems and business services since 1999, when Honeywell Inc. and
AlliedSignal Inc. merged.
</P>
<P>
   Porter will retain his current duties and will oversee the
company's human resources, communications and community affairs
divisions.
</P>
<P>
   Porter joined Honeywell Inc. in 1980 and held various positions
in the business unit and in human resources before being named
corporate vice president of human resources in 1993. He was named
vice president and chief administrative officer of Honeywell Inc.
in 1998.
</P>
<P>
   On the Net: www.honeywell.com
</P>
<P>
   CAMDEN, N.J. (AP) - The U.S. Postal Service will unveil its
newest collector stamps, Deep Sea Creatures, at the New Jersey
State Aquarium on Oct. 7.
</P>
<P>
   With the 1,500 inhabitants of the Deep Atlantic tank as the
backdrop, staff of the South Jersey District of the Postal service
will unveil the stamps at 11 a.m.
</P>
<P>
   ''The Postal service values its role as a community leader,''
said William J. Bothwell, acting district manager for the South
Jersey postal district. ''We believe our commemorative stamp
program gives us an opportunity to partner with local organizations
and connect with our customers in a very positive and entertaining
way.''
</P>
<P>
   The aquarium is located on the Delaware River waterfront.
</P>
<P>
   On the Net: www.njaquarium.org
</P>
