<HEADLINE> Perry Leaving N. Korea Policy Post  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- Former Defense Secretary William Perry is
stepping down from his post as coordinator for North Korea policy,
effective immediately, the State Department said Monday.
</P>
<P>
   No reason was given for his decision to step down.
</P>
<P>
   Wendy Sherman, who has worked closely with Perry since his
appointment in November 1998, will assume his duties and also serve
concurrently as counselor for the department, a post she has held
since 1997.
</P>
<P>
   Perry submitted a report to President Clinton a year ago
recommending that the United States seek an accommodation with
North Korea provided Pyongyang forgoes long-range missile and
nuclear weapons development.
</P>
</TEXT>
