<HEADLINE> 'Legends,' 'Exorcist' Top Releases  </HEADLINE>
By TOM HARRIGAN
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES (AP) -- The new horror film ''Urban Legends: Final
Cut'' claimed the top spot at the weekend box office over the
reissue of ''The Exorcist'' but only because it was in nearly four
times as many theaters.
</P>
<P>
   ''Urban Legends: Final Cut'' brought in $8.5 million on 2,539
movie screens, while ''The Exorcist'' earned $8.2 million at 664
locations. The re-edited film with some added scenes had an
estimated $165 million in gross receipts in the 1970s.
</P>
<P>
   The top 20 movies at North American theaters Friday through
Sunday, followed by distribution studio, gross, number of theater
locations, average receipts per location, total gross and number of
weeks in release, as compiled by Exhibitor Relations Co., Inc., and
ACNielsen Edi-Facts:
</P>
<P>
   1. ''Urban Legends: Final Cut,'' Sony, $8.5 million, 2,539
locations, $3,350 average, $8.5 million, one week.
</P>
<P>
   2. ''The Exorcist,'' Warner Bros., $8.2 million, 664 locations,
$12,286 average, $8.2 million, one week (reissue).
</P>
<P>
   3. ''Almost Famous,'' DreamWorks, $6.9 million, 1,193 locations,
$5,806 average, $10.1 million, two weeks.
</P>
<P>
   4. ''Bring it On,'' Universal, $4.3 million, 2,457 locations,
$1,740 average, $56 million, five weeks.
</P>
<P>
   5. ''The Watcher,'' Universal, $3.7 million, 2,777 locations,
$1,320 average, $22.8 million, three weeks.
</P>
<P>
   6. ''Bait,'' Warner Bros., $3.4 million, 2,352 locations, $1,431
average, $10.6 million, two weeks.
</P>
<P>
   7. ''Nurse Betty,'' USA, $3.3 million, 1,491 locations, $2,193
average, $18 million, three weeks.
</P>
<P>
   8. ''What Lies Beneath,'' DreamWorks, $2.19 million, 1,819
locations, $1,205 average, $148.4 million, 10 weeks.
</P>
<P>
   9. ''Space Cowboys,'' Warner Bros., $2.16 million, 2,170
locations, $994 average, $85.1 million, eight weeks.
</P>
<P>
   10. ''Woman On Top,'' Fox, $2 million, 1,085 locations, $1,851
average, $2 million, one week.
</P>
<P>
   11. ''The Cell,'' New Line, $1.6 million, 1,903 locations, $843
average, $57.4 million, six weeks.
</P>
<P>
   12. ''Scary Movie,'' Dimension, $1.3 million, 1,678 locations,
$782 average, $153.7 million, 12 weeks.
</P>
<P>
   13. ''Nutty Professor II: The Klumps,'' Universal, $1.2 million,
1,210 locations, $1,015 average, $120 million, nine weeks.
</P>
<P>
   14. ''The Replacements,'' Warner Bros., $1.14 million, 1,365
locations, $832 average, $42.5 million, seven weeks.
</P>
<P>
   15. ''The Original Kings of Comedy,'' Paramount, $1.11 million,
1,082 locations, $1,021 average, $35.5 million, six weeks.
</P>
<P>
   16. ''Duets,'' Disney, $935,004, 583 locations, $1,604 average,
$3.5 million, two weeks.
</P>
<P>
   17. ''The Art of War,'' Warner Bros., $831,130, 1,085 locations,
$766 average, $28.7 million, five weeks.
</P>
<P>
   18. ''Coyote Ugly,'' Disney, $813,097, 883 locations, $921
average, $57.8 million, eight weeks.
</P>
<P>
   19. ''Saving Grace,'' Fine Line, $694,240, 706 locations, $983
average, $10.7 million, eight weeks.
</P>
<P>
   20. ''Autumn in New York,'' MGM, $689,664, 1,182 locations, $583
average, $36.5 million, seven weeks.
</P>
