<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-25 23:12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Blues 2, Stars 2  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ST. LOUIS (AP) -- Ed Belfour overcame a shaky start in his first
preseason appearance, stopping the last 17 shots he faced in the
Dallas Stars' 2-2 tie with St. Louis on Monday night.
</P>
<P>
   Belfour, sidelined by a sore heel for the first five exhibition
games, allowed two goals on the first four shots he faced.
</P>
<P>
   Scott Young scored his third goal of the preseason at 41
seconds, getting a loose puck in the slot when a pass tipped off a
Stars player. Jochen Hecht made it 2-0 at 5:03 with the Blues
(2-2-2) on a 5-on-3 advantage.
</P>
<P>
   All of the scoring came in the first period. Blues goalie Roman
Turek, who made 25 saves, forced overtime when he stopped Brenden
Morrow on a breakaway with about two seconds left.
</P>
<P>
   Both teams had chances in the extra period, with the Blues' Sean
Hill whistled for tripping with 2:35 to go and the Stars' Mike
Modano called for hooking with 1:35 left. St. Louis' Mike Eastwood
hit the post just before Modano was sent off.
</P>
<P>
   Richard Matvichuk and Brett Hull tied it in the first period for
the Stars (3-1-2), who beat the Blues 4-2 on Sept. 16 in Dallas.
</P>
<P>
   Matvichuk's goal came on a power play at 14:44 and an off-ice
ruling helped the Stars tie it on Hull's second goal of the
preseason. The goal was awarded during a stoppage with less than
two minutes remaining in the first, and the clock was re-set to
four minutes -- the official time of the goal -- at that point.
</P>
<P>
   Hull shot glanced off Turek's glove and the crossbar, then the
back of Turek's leg before barely crossing the line. The goal light
briefly went on, but play went on.
</P>
<P>
   Young also had an assist for St. Louis and has six points in
four preseason games.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
