<HEADLINE> Army: Israeli Laser Passes Tests  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WHITE SANDS MISSILE RANGE, N.M. (AP) -- A combat laser designed
to protect northern Israel shot down two Russian-made rockets
during tests here, the Army reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
   The Tactical High Energy Laser, or THEL, successfully tracked,
then destroyed two Katyushas in flight on Friday. The laser is
being tested before deployment in Israel as a counterbalance to the
return of the Hezbollah guerrilla fighters and their Katyusha
rockets to the extreme south of neighboring Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
   Israel withdrew from a 10-mile strip of land inside Lebanon in
May after an 18-year occupation designed to keep Hezbollah out of
range.
</P>
</TEXT>
