<HEADLINE> Explosion rocks Suffolk gas station; area evacuated  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   EAST ISLIP, N.Y. (AP) - A section of East Islip was evacuated
Monday night after an explosion at a gas station shook houses up to
three blocks away and shot flames more than 100 feet in the air.
</P>
<P>
   There were no immediate reports of injury or death. Suffolk
County police and firefighters were having difficulty approaching
the area because of the intensity of the flames.
</P>
<P>
   The fire, possibly triggered when a delivery gas tanker collided
with a car, erupted at about 10:45 p.m. at a Sunoco station on
Montauk Highway.
</P>
<P>
   The immediate area was being evacuated.
</P>
<P>
   Residents up to three blocks away said they heard an explosion
that sounded like a plane crash and felt their houses tremble.
</P>
<P>
   More than an hour after the fire broke out, flames were still
shooting more than 50 feet high.
</P>
