<HEADLINE> Bomb Prank Clears Carrier  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEWPORT NEWS, Va. (AP) -- The Navy aircraft carrier USS Nimitz
was evacuated after a sailor discovered a toolbox with the words
''this is a bomb'' written on it, authorities said.
</P>
<P>
   Bomb squad technicians found only tools in the box on Friday and
declared the incident a prank. No one had been arrested as of
Monday, but the investigation was ongoing.
</P>
<P>
   Jerri Fuller Dickseski, a spokeswoman for Newport News
Shipbuilding, where the carrier is undergoing an overhaul, said
work crews lost about a half-day's pay because of the incident.
</P>
<P>
   The 95,000-ton nuclear-powered carrier is completing a $1.2
billion overhaul that started in 1998.
</P>
</TEXT>
